    <p class="caption" data-uuid="afd13fa1410e4e87a7ff0cfc59f5692b">After World War II, the United States and the Soviet Union engaged in a nuclear arms race. Here, American students practice a ”duck-and-cover drill,” designed to protect them from a nuclear bomb blast.</p>
