            <article data-uuid="2b384f3d92fb4a2fb62e9434860598e8">
                <h3 class="eq" data-uuid="95baf19acbbe4e5a8e6cdfa50efd174a">Essential Question</h3>
                <h3 class="eqt" data-uuid="ec1d070fde9a4ad18264fbb91d8f7e74">How might the Cold War have been prevented?</h3>
                <p data-uuid="eda77fbe562442f386531058a98576ae">As World War II ended, major differences arose
                    between the Soviet Union and the United States. The two nations became
                    adversaries, engaged in a power struggle that came to be called the Cold War.
                    This struggle was costly and led to conflicts around the world as each tried to
                    protect its interests. Could this struggle have been prevented?</p>
                <p data-uuid="556dfa0530744fc59487494d07516681">As you read this module, look for evidence of the political and ideological
                    differences of the two nations. Note the key people, decisions, circumstances,
                    and turning points that resulted in Cold War tensions. When you are done,
                    you will write a short essay answering the Essential Question for this module.</p>
            </article>
            <section class="video-container " data-uuid="24e77361fd0c4a10a98668e5889e4fcb">
                <article data-uuid="affae066f9734804b9a45885ec7818cf">
                    <h3 class="vid" data-uuid="127de60a4ddb465b8e1d3a5640cab915">The Arms Race</h3>
                    <p class="vid" data-uuid="2aff7cb90c054a54a22546f9de043eb1"></p>
                    <p data-uuid="611327017c5a4c039a4c35d401ead504">The postwar struggle for power
                        between the United States and the Soviet Union led each country to develop more and more powerful
                        weapons. Only a few years after the United States used the atomic bomb in World War II,
                        the Soviet Union had also developed an atomic bomb. The arms race had begun.</p>
