                    <h3 class="mod" data-uuid="edc44c503aad4f5ab6c5a3ba9645283e">The Cold War 1945–1960</h3>
                    <p class="mod" data-uuid="ff63455d32454fc399aef7c3c0cc4f6e">The Allies put aside their differences to fight their
                        common enemy in World War II, but those differences were not gone. As the war ended, the
                        division built into what became known as an “iron curtain.” Throughout
                        the Cold War, the United States and the USSR, engaged in a
                        contest of action/reaction. Each side tried to stay ahead of the other in
                        territory, weapons, and even in space.</p>
                </article>
